CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1774105895
OL,3,CRare glimpse into life of famous
OL,4,Cfossil-finder reveals she got sick of
OL,5,Cher hobby
OL,7,FTom Sharpe who has written books on
OL,8,FMary Anning said: "There is no better
OL,9,For more appropriate home for this
OL,10,Fletter fragment, an exceptionally rare
OL,11,Fexample of a personal, not business-
OL,12,Frelated, letter of Anning's.
OL,14,F"Bringing this autographed letter
OL,15,Ffragment home to Lyme Regis allows it
OL,16,Fto be seen and interpreted in the
OL,17,Fcontext of the place where it was
OL,18,Fwritten and offers visitors a direct
OL,19,Fand tangible connection across two
OL,20,Fcenturies with Mary Anning."
OL,26,@pD@SOUvD@AOU|D@\O]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
